Package de.wwu.muggl.instructions.interfaces.data

Provides interfaces for marking the behaviour of instructions with regard to the datal-flow.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
OtherFrameStackPush The implementing instruction is known to push an element onto the operand stack of another but the currently executed frame.
StackPop The implementing instruction is known to pop at least one element from the operand stack of the currently executed frame.
StackPush The implementing instruction is known to push an element onto the operand stack of the currently executed frame.
VariableDefining The implementing instruction is known to define a variable in the sense of data-flow tracking.
VariableLoading The implementing instruction is known to load a variable in the sense of data-flow tracking.
VariableUsing The implementing instruction is known to use a variable in the sense of data-flow tracking.Please note that the wide instruction will not be marked by this interface, even though it (among others) provides widened access to store.
VariablyStackPop The implementing instruction is known to pop at least one element from the operand stack of the currently executed frame.
VariablyStackPush The implementing instruction is known to push an element onto the operand stack of the currently executed frame.
